# Azure DevOps CLI — macOS authentication

Before any `az devops` / `az pipelines` / Azure DevOps CLI skill command on macOS, ensure the
session is authenticated. **Never** commit PATs or print `AZURE_DEVOPS_EXT_PAT`.

## One-time Keychain setup

```bash
security add-generic-password -a "$USER" -s AZDO_PAT -w "YOUR_PAT" -U
```

## Login (every new shell / before ADO CLI work)

```bash
azdo-login() {
  export AZURE_DEVOPS_EXT_PAT="$(security find-generic-password -s AZDO_PAT -w)"
  az devops login --organization https://dev.azure.com/petrovskyitools
}
```

Run `azdo-login` before Azure DevOps CLI operations. The function sets `AZURE_DEVOPS_EXT_PAT`
and logs `az` into org **petrovskyitools**.

Optional: add the function to `~/.zshrc`, or source
`skills/azure-devops-cli/templates/azdo-login-macos.zsh` (supports `AZDO_ORG` override).

## Agent / CI

- **macOS local:** run `azdo-login` in the terminal (or ensure PAT is already exported).
- **CI / Linux:** pipeline secret → `AZURE_DEVOPS_EXT_PAT` — no Keychain.
- Do not paste PATs into chat, commits, or logs.
